      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While the urgency of climate change is undeniable, saying nuclear risks are irrelevant is a leap, as catastrophic accidents retain severe, long-term consequences. Meeting aggressive climate targets with just wind and solar requires massive, incredibly reliable energy storage solutions that are not yet commercially scalable enough for a global baseload. Therefore, many climate models suggest that a diversified energy portfolio, including nuclear, is necessary to provide the constant, reliable power needed to fully replace fossil fuels.",
      "source": "target",
